hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Start with 
$$Y_7 = \frac{A\,R_p}{B\,R_d + C\,R_p}\,. $$
Since $R_p\propto S_{34}$ and $R_d$, $A$, $B$, $C$ are independent of $S_{34}$, we have 
$$\frac{\partial\ln Y_7}{\partial\ln S_{34}}
=\frac{\partial\ln Y_7}{\partial\ln R_p}\,. $$

2. Write
$$\ln Y_7 = \ln A + \ln R_p - \ln\bigl(B R_d + C R_p\bigr)\,. $$
Differentiating with respect to $\ln R_p$ gives
$$\frac{\partial\ln Y_7}{\partial\ln R_p}
=1 - \frac{C R_p}{B R_d + C R_p}
=\frac{B R_d}{B R_d + C R_p}\,. $$

3. Given $C R_p = f\,B R_d$ with $f=\tfrac19$, substitute:
$$\frac{B R_d}{B R_d + C R_p}
=\frac{B R_d}{B R_d + f\,B R_d}
=\frac{1}{1+f}
=\frac{1}{1+\tfrac19}
=\frac{9}{10}\,. $$

Thus 
$$\frac{\partial\ln Y_7}{\partial\ln S_{34}}=\frac{9}{10}\,. $$
